Doc Del:<br><br>
I guess it shouldn't come as too much of a surprise to either of us to recognize the parallels that exist between American Indians and Orientals.  We come from a common gene pool... it makes sense that we may share something else.<br>
An interesting study deals with Shame vs. Guilt.  Nope! They are not the same.  Very similiar but still diferent.<br>
Native Americans are prone to shame... &quot;I fell on my ass in front of the people!  Surely they must think that I am clumbsey and stupid!&quot;... an exterior locus of control.<br>
Western European Protestant thinkers embrace guilt more readily, an internal locus of control, &quot;Mommie told me not to take a cookie from the cookie jar.. but I took one anyway... I am a sneaky thief.&quot;<br>
Since I don't eat buffalo meat for breakfast and I spend half my time at Wal Mart... I suppose that I, as most Indian folks, now have a dose of shame and guilt... a crappy gift from those Spam eatin', pumpkin rolling, bicycle seat sniffing, fishing fanatics, Chevy driving invaders from Europe.  What have we ever done to you guys... except pass a few counterfiet Indian artifacts made in Taiwan?<br><br>
Humming Eagle<br><br>
P.S.  What do fish taste like?
